# KIS-Points Prototype 1 - Cursor Rules (Dual Shell & Zustand)

**Canonical reference:** `docs/architecture-plan.md` (folder map, exceptions, sync mounting). Feature-first component layout: `docs/featureFirstMigrationPlan.md` (complete May 2026).

## 0. `src/app/` — frozen thin routes

* **Policy:** `src/app/` is the routing table only. Do **not** modify anything under `src/app/` unless the user or task **explicitly** requires a new/changed route, URL, segment `layout.tsx` wire, or a Next.js framework boundary (e.g. `Suspense` around client hooks in `app/dashboard/layout.tsx`).
* **Stay dumb:** `page.tsx` and segment `layout.tsx` should stay ~5–10 lines — one shell or view import, one default export. No hooks, stores, Supabase, or orchestration. If a route file grows or needs hooks → move logic to `src/features/`.
* **Dashboard split (do not collapse):** `app/dashboard/layout.tsx` → `DashboardShell` only; `app/dashboard/**/page.tsx` → `<DashboardView />` only. Do **not** hoist `DashboardView` into layout for DRY unless there is an explicit, documented architecture decision.
* **Symmetric dashboard pages:** `page.tsx` and `classes/[classId]/page.tsx` both render `<DashboardView />` from `@/features/dashboard/DashboardView.tsx` only. Do not duplicate pathname/`key` logic or stage routing in `app/` routes.
* **Dashboard stage entry:** `@/features/dashboard/DashboardView.tsx` — sync workers + `activeView` routing in one file. Do not split routing back into `app/` or reintroduce `DashboardViewSwitch`.

## 1. Architectural Mandate: The Dual-Shell System

You must identify the active shell before applying layout or state rules. They are visually and logically isolated.

### A. Auth & Landing Shell (The Entryway)

* **Scope (URLs):** `/`, `/login`, `/signup`, `/forgot-password`, `/reset-password`.
* **Routes (filesystem):** `src/app/(landing)/page.tsx` → `/`; `src/app/(auth)/login|signup|forgot-password|reset-password/page.tsx` (route groups; URLs unchanged).
* **Tier 1 (landing):** `@/features/landing/layouts/LandingShell.tsx` (pass-through for now); `src/app/(landing)/layout.tsx` imports it only.
* **Tier 1 (auth routes):** `@/features/auth/layouts/AuthShell.tsx` (flex centering chrome); `src/app/(auth)/layout.tsx` imports it only (mirrors `app/dashboard/layout.tsx` → `DashboardShell`).
* **Tier 2 views:** `@/features/auth/*View` (wire `useAuthFlow` + Tier 3 forms only — do not reintroduce a layout wrapper in views), `@/features/landing/LandingView.tsx`.
* **Tier 3 UI:** `@/features/auth/components/` (forms + chrome), `@/features/landing/components/`.
* **Layout Logic:** Uses **Flexbox** for centering (e.g., `flex items-center justify-center`).
* **State:** **No Global Zustand Store.** Use `useAuthFlow.ts` for local form/UI state.
* **Session:** Layer 1 hook + `@/lib/api/auth.service.ts` (Layer 3).
* **Rule:** Do not move auth views into `components/` for folder-policy reasons. Auth/landing UI belongs in `@/features/{auth,landing}/components/`, not `components/ui/`.

### B. Dashboard Shell (The Workspace)

* **Scope:** `/dashboard/`, `/dashboard/classes/[classId]`.
* **Shell (Tier 1):** `@/features/dashboard/layouts/DashboardShell.tsx` (7-zone grid; mounted from `app/dashboard/layout.tsx`).
* **Stage entry (Tier 2):** `@/features/dashboard/DashboardView.tsx` — mounted from dashboard `page.tsx`; sync workers, pathname `key`, route guard, `ClassesView` / `StudentsView`.
* **Frame (Tier 1):** `@/features/dashboard/components/frame/` — shell chrome only (`navbars/`, `StageTwoColumnLayout`, `dashboardZoneConfig`); no `DashboardView.tsx` under frame.
* **Folder policy:** Dashboard **Tier 3** → `@/features/{dashboard,classes,students,seating}/components/`; shared atoms → `@/components/ui/`. **Tier 2** → `@/features/`.
* **Imports (moving forward):** Use `@/features/<feature>/components/...` for feature UI. **Never** recreate `@/components/dashboard/` or `@/components/ui/auth|landing/`.
* **Modal host (Tier 2):** `@/features/dashboard/DashboardClassModalsHost.tsx` (mounted in `DashboardShell`).
* **Tools host (Tier 2):** `@/features/dashboard/DashboardToolsHost.tsx` — Timer via `@/components/ui/MovableToolPanel.tsx`; Random via `@/components/ui/LargeToolModal.tsx` (90% viewport). `BottomNav` opens via `setTimerOpen` / `setRandomOpen`. Canvas always `{children}`.
* **Award / edit-skills (Tier 2 + Layer 1):** `@/features/dashboard/AwardPointsModalHost.tsx` + `hooks/useAwardPointsModalController.ts`; `@/features/dashboard/EditSkillsModalHost.tsx` + `hooks/useEditSkillsModalController.ts`. Prefer this **host + controller** pattern when a dashboard modal subtree needs orchestration hooks but the UI itself should stay Tier 3.
* **Layout Logic:** Shell chrome grid (`dashboardZoneConfig.ts`); main stage 2-column layout is **view-owned** (`StageTwoColumnLayout` + per-view toolbar).
* **State:** `useUserStore`, `useDashboardStore` (includes `absentStudentIds` for daily attendance), `useLayoutStore`, `useSeatingStore`, `useModalStore`, `usePreferenceStore`.
* **Source of Truth:** The **URL** is the primary source of truth for `classId`, `view`, and `mode`.
* **Rule:** Do not apply dashboard grid rules to auth/landing, or auth flex rules to the dashboard workspace.
* **App folder:** See **§0** — off-limits for refactors; dashboard pages import `DashboardView` only.

---

## 2. Visual 3-Tier / Data 3-Layer Boundaries

### Tier 1: Scaffolding (The Building) — dashboard only

* **Locations:** `@/features/dashboard/components/frame/` (includes `navbars/`, `StageTwoColumnLayout.tsx`, `dashboardZoneConfig.ts`).
* **Responsibility:** Persistent chrome and CSS Grid boundaries.
* **Rule:** `DashboardClassesSync` in `DashboardShell`; `app/dashboard/layout.tsx` is Suspense + shell wire only; `useDashboardRouteStateSync` / `useViewPreferenceSync` in `DashboardShell`; class/student/profile/filter sync + stage routing in `@/features/dashboard/DashboardView.tsx`; dashboard `page.tsx` files render `<DashboardView />` only.
* **Allowed:** Narrow store reads in navbars for chrome (e.g., `activeClassId`, `viewMode`). No Supabase, no mutation orchestration.

### Tier 2: The Stage (The Sets) — dashboard only

* **Locations:** `@/features/dashboard/`, `@/features/classes/`, `@/features/students/`, `@/features/seating/`.
* **Responsibility:** View orchestration, workspace wiring, store subscription, passing props to Tier 3.
* **Includes:** `features/dashboard/stage/` (`dashboardToolbarConfig.ts`, `DashboardCanvasToolbar`, presets), `features/classes/components/ClassesCanvasToolbar.tsx`, `features/students/components/StudentsStageToolbar.tsx`, `features/seating/SeatingEditorCanvasToolbar.tsx`, `features/dashboard/tools/Random.tsx`, `DashboardToolsHost.tsx`, `DashboardClassModalsHost.tsx`, **`AwardPointsModalHost.tsx`**, **`EditSkillsModalHost.tsx`**, `features/classes/EditClassModalRoot.tsx`, `features/seating/SeatingGroupsCanvas.tsx`.
* **New modal flows:** If a modal needs `@/hooks` orchestration (`use*` data, mutations, icons), implement **`features/dashboard/MyFeatureModalHost.tsx`** + **`hooks/useMyFeatureModalController.ts`**, expose `*ViewProps` next to **`features/dashboard/components/modals/MyFeatureModal.tsx`**. Do not bolt Layer 1 hooks onto presentational Tier 3 modals/forms by default.
* **Nested UI:** Tier 3 modals may import and render Tier 2 **hosts** for self-contained subtrees (e.g. `AwardPointsModal` → `EditSkillsModalHost`); do not merge unrelated controller logic into a single hook.
* **Rules:**
  * Use **granular selectors** to prevent re-renders.
  * ✅ `const students = useDashboardStore(s => s.students)`
  * ❌ `const { students } = useDashboardStore()`
  * **No runtime** `@/lib/api/*` calls; type-only imports are OK.
  * Prefer `@/stores/dashboardStudentSelectors.ts` for roster ordering/aggregates.

### Tier 3: The Actors (Pure UI)

* **Locations:** `@/components/ui/` (shared primitives, icons, `CanvasToolbar.tsx`). Feature UI: `@/features/dashboard/components/`, `@/features/classes/components/`, `@/features/students/components/`, `@/features/seating/components/`, `@/features/auth/components/`, `@/features/landing/components/`.
* **Responsibility:** Presentational UI. Props in via props, behaviors out via callbacks. Local UI state (`useState`, refs, narrow `useEffect` for UX) allowed.
* **Rules:** No **stores**, no **`@/hooks`** for **orchestration** (data fetch, mutations, cross-store flows), no API clients unless type-only imports. Thin modal wrappers that only compose children are OK.
* **`forms/AddSkillForm.tsx`** and **`forms/EditSkillForm.tsx`** — **strict Tier 3:** no `@/hooks`; parent controllers (`useAwardPointsModalController`, `useEditSkillsModalController`) supply icon arrays / detecting flags / submit handlers passed through **`AddSkillModal`** / **`EditSkillModal`**.
* **Cross-tier import:** Tier 3 modals under `features/dashboard/components/modals/` may import **`@/features/dashboard/*Host`** only for nested gated flows—not for workspaces.
* **Documented exceptions** (see `docs/architecture-plan.md`):
  * `StudentCard.tsx` — `useShallow` store slice for grid performance.
  * `EditSkillsModal.tsx` — presentational; wiring via `useEditSkillsModalController` + `features/dashboard/EditSkillsModalHost.tsx`.
  * `AwardPointsModal.tsx` — presentational; wiring via `useAwardPointsModalController` + `features/dashboard/AwardPointsModalHost.tsx`.
  * `features/classes/components/modals/EditClassModal.tsx` — thin façade re-exporting `EditClassModalRoot`.
  * `features/dashboard/components/tools/Timer.tsx` — Tier 3 timer body; `DashboardToolsHost` + `MovableToolPanel`.
  * `features/dashboard/tools/Random.tsx` — Tier 2 random tool; `DashboardToolsHost` + `LargeToolModal` (not canvas ternary).

---

## 3. The 7-Zone Fixed Grid (Dashboard Only)

The Dashboard is a fixed coordinate system. Do not use these rules for Auth/Landing pages.

* **Zone 1:** Persistent Left Nav.
* **Zones 2 & 3:** Top Bar / Header.
* **Zones 4 & 5:** Main stage — `StageTwoColumnLayout` in Tier-2 views (canvas + right toolbar rail); not split in `DashboardShell`.
* **Zones 6 & 7:** Bottom Bar / Footer.
* **Constraint:** Use `h-full` or `min-h-0` inside the Stage. **Never use `h-screen`** inside Dashboard content.

---

## 4. Strict Data Flow Rules

### Layer 1: Orchestrators (`@/hooks/`)

* **Pattern:** UI Event → Hook → Update Zustand (Layer 2) → Persist to Supabase (Layer 3).
* **Dashboard modal subgraphs:** Use dedicated **`use*ModalController`** hooks with matching **`features/dashboard/*ModalHost.tsx`** instead of attaching orchestration hooks to Tier 3 modals/forms (see award points / edit skills).
* **Optimistic UI:** Always update the store immediately for point awards or roster changes. Roll back on Layer 3 failure.

### Layer 1b: Route & store sync (`@/hooks/sync/`)

* **Responsibility:** Renderless workers aligning URL ↔ stores (e.g., `useDashboardRouteStateSync`, `useDashboardStudentSync`, `DashboardClassesSync`).
* **Rule:** Do not mirror shareable state with ad hoc `useEffect` in Tier 1/2 components when a sync hook exists.

### Layer 2: The Desk (`@/stores/`)

* **Constraint:** **Zustand stores MUST NOT import Supabase.** They are pure data containers.
* **Forbidden:** React Context is strictly forbidden for global application state.

### Layer 3: The Vault (`@/lib/api/`)

* **Constraint:** **Dumb Data Access.** Parameters in, typed records out. No React or Zustand knowledge.
* **Rule:** Supabase clients only in Layer 3, orchestrated by Layer 1 hooks — never from Tier 2/3 UI at runtime.

---

## 5. Development Best Practices

* **TypeScript:** Strictly type all props and store shapes in `@/lib/types.ts`. **Avoid `any` at all costs.**
* **Naming conventions:**
  * `use...Service.ts` / `use...Actions.ts` — hooks handling data persistence and orchestration.
  * `use...Sync.ts` / `*Sync.tsx` — renderless workers aligning URL/state.
  * `attendanceService.ts` — Layer 3 API module (not `useAttendanceService`).
* **Selectors:** Subscribe to the smallest possible slice for large rosters (30+ students).
* **Absolute positioning:** Permitted **only** for internal UI styling (icons, mascots). Must be contained within a `relative` parent that respects the grid.

---

## 6. Seating editor canvas toolbar (Dashboard)

Applies when URL/layout reflect **seating chart + edit mode** (`?view=seating` + `?mode=edit`, `useLayoutStore.isEditMode`).

* **Mount (Tier 1):** `DashboardShell` renders `SeatingEditorCanvasToolbar` in the canvas toolbar column instead of `DashboardCanvasToolbar`. Toolbar column uses `overflow-visible` in edit mode.
* **Left nav:** `SeatingEditorLeftNav` replaces default left nav (layout list).
* **Footer:** Keep `BottomNav` — pass `buttonsDisabled={isSeatingView && isEditMode}`. **Do not** reintroduce `SeatingEditorBottomNav`.
* **Stage (Tier 2):** `StudentsWorkspace` → `SeatingChartEditorView` while editing; `SeatingChartView` when not.

### Toolbar ownership

| Piece | Location |
|-------|----------|
| Toolbar orchestration | `features/seating/SeatingEditorCanvasToolbar.tsx` (Tier 2) |
| Toolbar shell | `components/ui/CanvasToolbar.tsx` (Tier 3) |
| Preset actions (Close, layout manager, …) | `features/dashboard/stage/canvasToolbarPresets.tsx` + `hooks/dashboard/useCanvasToolbarActions.ts` |
| Editor settings/groups/randomize | `hooks/useSeatingEditBottomNav.ts` (name is legacy; powers toolbar, not a bottom nav) |
| Menu UI | `features/seating/components/menus/SeatingViewSettingsMenu.tsx`, `SeatingSettingsMenu.tsx`, `SeatingEditorAddGroupsMenu.tsx` |

### Portaled dropdowns

* Render menus with `createPortal(..., document.body)` and position via `useAnchoredDropdownPortal`.
* **Top-slot menus** (View Settings): `placement: 'leftOfAnchorDown'`.
* **Bottom-slot menus** (Settings, Add Groups): `placement: 'leftOfAnchorAbove'`.
* Pass `isToolbarMenu`, `menuClassName`, and portal `style` into Tier 3 menus; do not rely on `absolute bottom-full` inside the toolbar column.
* Close other bottom-slot menus when opening one (avoid stacked portaled menus).

### Exit edit mode

Toolbar Close (X) dispatches `STAGE_CLOSE_EDITOR` → `useSeatingChart.ts` / route sync clears `isEditMode` → `SeatingChartView` + enabled `BottomNav`.

---

## 7. Student attendance (Dashboard)

Table DDL: `docs/db-schema.md` §5. Architecture flow: `docs/architecture-plan.md` §2.1–§2.2.

### Layers (do not blur boundaries)

* **Layer 3:** `attendanceService.ts` only — no React/Zustand.
* **Layer 2:** `absentStudentIds` on `useDashboardStore` — no API calls in store actions.
* **Layer 1:** `useAttendanceActions` — optimistic toggle + silent rollback; no UI.
* **Layer 1b:** `useAttendanceSync` / `AttendanceSync` — hydrate on class change; mount in `DashboardView` with other sync workers (recommended; see architecture plan).
* **Tier 3:** `@/features/students/components/menus/AttendanceMenuBody.tsx` — props/callbacks only; **no** `@/stores` or `@/hooks` for orchestration.
* **Tier 1 chrome:** `@/features/dashboard/components/frame/navbars/BottomNav.tsx` may wire store + hooks + `createPortal` bottom sheet (`data-attendance-menu`); use Tailwind transitions, not Framer Motion.

### Point awards with absent students

* **Bulk modes** (`wholeClass`, `multiClass`): filter via `filterEligibleStudentIds` / `toEligibleStudentIds`; return early if none eligible.
* **Seating group batch:** use `openMultiStudentPointsAward(ids, { excludeAbsent: true })` from `useBatchPointsAward.ts` — do not call `openModal` directly for new seating batch flows.
* **Manual multi-select award** and **single-student award:** do **not** filter absent (teacher override allowed).
* **`selectAll`** in `useStudentsSelection`: exclude `absentStudentIds`; leave `handleSelectStudent` unchanged.

### Forbidden for attendance work

* Do not add attendance API calls inside Tier 3 components or Zustand store actions.
* Do not filter absent students from manual multi-select awards unless product explicitly changes override rules.
